Quantity (Part VI)
16. Conclusion

This summary cites about 110 of the definitions in PM. The last eight
pages (667–674) of Volume I of the second edition (1925)
consists of a complete list of 498 definitions from all three volumes.
Correspondence in the Bertrand Russell Archives confirms that this was
compiled by Dorothy Wrinch. Her list can be used to trace every one of
the other defined expressions of PM back to the notation discussed in
this entry.
